# WASM artifacts are COMMITTED (not gitignored) so npm publish can
# ship a working package without requiring a local emsdk build. The
# tradeoff is a ~1.3 MB binary in git history; in exchange, consumers
# `npm install @rdm7/sandbox` and it Just Works. Rebuilt via
# scripts/build.ps1 whenever the C side changes.

# User-local IDE/agent config.
.claude/

# Synced firmware sources (pulled via scripts/sync-firmware.ps1)
# Kept out of git to avoid double-ownership with the firmware repo.
firmware_src/
